# V23.3 A1.a (wiki/380): repo-root .dockerignore.
# Buildah/docker only reads .dockerignore at the BUILD CONTEXT root.
# The bridge image build (musu-relay/installer/build-musu-backend.sh
# step 3.d) uses repo root as context (Dockerfile lives at
# musu-bridge/Dockerfile; context must include musu-core/ sibling).
#
# Builder note (wiki/380 §12 amendment): the plan placed .dockerignore at
# musu-bridge/.dockerignore — that file is NOT read by buildah when the
# context is repo root. Without these rules, host __pycache__/ inside
# musu-core/src/musu_core/ leaks into the COPY layer, breaking B6
# byte-identity (Build A vs Build B mismatch on the COPY layer's tar).
# Rules below are scoped to the directories the bridge Dockerfile actually
# COPYs from (musu-bridge/ and musu-core/), so other potential users of
# the repo root as context are not affected by accidental over-exclusion.

# musu-bridge/ exclusions (mirror the original musu-bridge/.dockerignore)
musu-bridge/.venv/
musu-bridge/.venv*/
musu-bridge/__pycache__/
musu-bridge/**/__pycache__/
musu-bridge/**/*.pyc
musu-bridge/**/*.pyo
musu-bridge/**/*.pyd
musu-bridge/.pytest_cache/
musu-bridge/.mypy_cache/
musu-bridge/nohup.out
musu-bridge/**/*.log
musu-bridge/tests/
musu-bridge/test_*.py
musu-bridge/*_test.py
musu-bridge/**/*.bak
musu-bridge/.git/
# S-A1a-H1 (security audit, wiki/381): exclude dev/QA/legacy/template
# artifacts that ship under /app/ as information-disclosure surface
# (OWASP A05:2021). These are tracked in git so .gitignore does not
# stop the COPY; only .dockerignore at build-context root does.
musu-bridge/.musu/
musu-bridge/_legacy_*/
musu-bridge/.env
musu-bridge/.env.*
musu-bridge/*.example
musu-bridge/instructions/
musu-bridge/Dockerfile
musu-bridge/Dockerfile.*
# Critic L5 from plan §12 wanted Dockerfile/.dockerignore/requirements-lock.txt
# excluded so they don't clutter the runtime /app/. The repo-root .dockerignore
# cannot exclude them: requirements-lock.txt is needed by the explicit
# `COPY musu-bridge/requirements-lock.txt /tmp/` step, and excluding it would
# block the entire build. The cost of letting all three ship under /app/ at
# runtime is ~3 KB; acceptable. To revisit (image-bytes-tight), switch the
# wholesale `COPY musu-bridge/ /app/` to use BuildKit 1.7 `--exclude` flags
# on the second COPY rather than dockerignore — that's COPY-scoped, not
# context-scoped, and resolves the conflict cleanly.

# Static assets are INCLUDED by default (F13). Uncomment to exclude when
# image-size pressure forces (A1.c bench follow-on).
# musu-bridge/static/novnc/

# musu-core/ exclusions — only the bridge image COPYs musu_core,
# so __pycache__ leakage here is what was breaking B6 byte-identity.
musu-core/**/__pycache__/
musu-core/**/*.pyc
musu-core/**/*.pyo
musu-core/**/*.pyd
musu-core/.pytest_cache/
musu-core/.mypy_cache/
musu-core/tests/
musu-core/**/*.bak
